text: Angie Forsett (born June 6, 1986) is an American volleyball player. She was a member of the United States women's national volleyball team. == Career == She played at 2009 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2010 Montreux Volley Masters, 2011 Montreux Volley Masters, 2011 Pan American Cup, and 2011 Pan American Games, where she won a bronze medal. She played for University of California, Berkeley's women's volleyball team and Llaneras de Toa Baja. She married Justin Forsett. == References == Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:American volleyball players
